This paper deals with routing in sensor networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of geographic information and location-based routing, which is a topic that falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of information theory to analyze the performance of routing strategies, which is a topic that falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of progressive routing strategies, which is a topic that falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the analysis of routing delays and throughput-capacity, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
